value: Central America, South America: se Mexico to ne Argentina

Montane Evergreen Forest, Tropical Lowland Evergreen Forest (0-2500 m; Tropical and Subtropical zones). Elevational range shifts from lowlands at northern edge of range (e.g., 0-350 in Guatemala), to foothills in middle portion of range (e.g., 400-1200 m in Honduras), to foothill and lower montane forests at southern end (e.g., 700-2200 m, in Costa Rica).
